When I was ~15 years old I remember going to the mountains with a buddy in spring for the first time and sensing an absolute euphoria as we climbed to the peaks, just infinite energy, running and jumping over cliffs with zero fear of falling, feeling immortal, a pure radiant joy.

Like both of us couldn't stop laughing, climbing various rocks and putting ourselves in idiotic dangerous places. I never get that high level of euphoria nowadays in the mountains, even by the end of high school. Dr. Peat is right that puberty does forever "suppress" something.

I still get the "metaphysical" triumph at the top that Evola also described, the respiratory rejuvenation of mountain air, good mood, an open appetite, etc. but that one day for a few hours I genuinely felt like a god. A perfect organism in a perfect environment. A literal peak.
